2013-08-07  ChangZhuo Chen (é™³æ˜Œå€¬) <czchen@gmail.com>

	* .travis.yml, CMakeLists.txt: Add `make check' in cmake build cmake does not auto build test program when using `make test' [1].
	It causes some problem because developer might test the old code
	instead of the latest one. In order to avoid such issue, a new
	target called `make check' is added to cmake [2].  [1]

	http://stackoverflow.com/questions/733475/cmake-ctest-make-test-doesnt-build-tests[2] http://www.cmake.org/Wiki/CMakeEmulateMakeCheck

